		{
			"name": "WebSocket - /ws/chat",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "WebSocket Connection Test",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{ws_base_url}}/ws/chat",
							"host": [
								"{{ws_base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"ws",
								"chat"
							]
						},
						"description": "WebSocket endpoint connection test.\n\n**To test WebSocket in Postman:**\n1. Click on 'New' -> 'WebSocket Request'\n2. Enter URL: `ws://localhost:8000/ws/chat`\n3. Click 'Connect'\n4. Send JSON messages:\n```json\n{\n    \"session_id\": \"ws_user_1\",\n    \"message\": \"I want to book a room.\"\n}\n```\n\n**Expected Response:**\nYou should receive:\n1. Status message: `{\"type\": \"status\", \"message\": \"Processing your request...\"}`\n2. Streaming tokens as plain text\n3. Completion: `{\"type\": \"done\", \"message\": \"Response complete\"}`"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "WebSocket endpoint tests. Use Postman's WebSocket feature to test real-time streaming.\n\n**WebSocket Test Instructions:**\n\n1. Open Postman and create a new WebSocket Request\n2. URL: `ws://localhost:8000/ws/chat`\n3. Connect to the WebSocket\n4. Send test messages in JSON format:\n\n**Test Message 1 - Initial Booking:**\n```json\n{\n    \"session_id\": \"ws_user_1\",\n    \"message\": \"I want to book a room.\"\n}\n```\n\n**Test Message 2 - Follow-up:**\n```json\n{\n    \"session_id\": \"ws_user_1\",\n    \"message\": \"What are your room rates?\"\n}\n```\n\n**Test Message 3 - Different Session:**\n```json\n{\n    \"session_id\": \"ws_user_2\",\n    \"message\": \"What time is check-in?\"\n}\n```\n\n**Test Message 4 - Cancellation Policy:**\n```json\n{\n    \"session_id\": \"ws_user_3\",\n    \"message\": \"I need to cancel my reservation. What is your policy?\"\n}\n```\n\n**Expected WebSocket Responses:**\n- Status: `{\"type\": \"status\", \"message\": \"Processing your request...\"}`\n- Tokens: Streaming text chunks (plain text)\n- Done: `{\"type\": \"done\", \"message\": \"Response complete\"}`\n- Errors: `{\"type\": \"error\", \"message\": \"error details\"}`"
		},
